# Cursor Global Rules

- Use JSDoc type annotations consistently for all functions and classes. Do not introduce TypeScript unless the project is migrated to it.
- Follow Test-Driven Development (TDD). Write tests before or alongside implementation code.
- Do not use external APIs, databases, or any persistence layer. All data must be stored in-memory using JavaScript collections.
- All services must depend on abstractions (constructor injection), not on concrete implementations directly.
